      h1 Overview
      hr.accent
      div.text 
        p The postpaid model allows user to pay after making a series of purchases. It is an alternative to pay-per-use because it aggregates micro transacations into a single bill as opposed to charging users individually.
      h1 Advantages
      hr.accent
      div.text 
        ul.textList
         li Merchants benefit from impulse buying, as discussed in prepaid
         li Just like with the prepaid model, aggregating payments allows merchants to incur reduced transaction fees
         li Users do not feel any obligation to purchase a certain amount of the service as they are only billed for what they consume, unlike with the prepaid model where their prepayment represents a fixed quantity of the merchantâ€™s service
      h1 Disadvantages
      hr.accent
      div.text 
        ul.textList
         li If users purchase a single item, say a $1.99 article, and not anything else, merchants will have to process the sole transaction and incur processing fees.
         li This model makes services less accessible to the underbanked as it requires a debit or credit card to make payments
    
